
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `desktop2menu` baraye dorost kardane menu az file-haye `.desktop` dar pooshe-ye `~/Desktop` estefade mishavad. In dastoor barname-ha ra dar menu-ye system shoma ezafe mikonad.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 Hich gozine-ye khas nadarad.

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ desktop2menu

    🔹 Ezafe kardane shortcut-haye barname-ha az Desktop be menu.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    agar shoma file `.desktop` dar desktop darid, ba ejraye dastoor `desktop2menu` , yek shortcut az an barname dar menu system ijad mishavad.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `desktop2menu` command is used to create menu entries from `.desktop` files located in the `~/Desktop` directory. This command effectively adds applications to your system's menu.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 This command doesn't typically have any specific options.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ desktop2menu

    🔹 Adds application shortcuts from the Desktop to the menu.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    If you have a `.desktop` file on your desktop, running `desktop2menu` will create a shortcut for that application in the system menu.

